Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.44,0:00:15.04,OP,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I want to shine on you,\Nand always like that dazzling sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.35,0:00:18.72,OP,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I will defend you\Nfrom all the darkness.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.82,0:00:24.72,OP,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,This is the truth from my heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.72,0:00:39.50,OP,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If only our hearts could connect,\NI could get you to believe me.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.60,0:00:46.28,OP,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Even if you can't\Nsee it now, don't lose it.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.44,0:00:54.22,OP,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Your kindness won't be in vain.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.05,0:01:01.62,OP,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You'll be carried aloft by the wind\Nto somewhere that isn't here.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.03,0:01:08.73,OP,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You'll cross the sea and cross time,\Nand I know you'll blossom one day.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.90,0:01:15.37,OP,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Whatever the day,\NI'll be there for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.81,0:01:22.01,OP,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I hope I can watch over you\Nlike the sun for all time.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.01,0:01:31.99,OP,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,This is the truth from my heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.84,0:01:54.71,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It's still here!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.65,0:02:02.52,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Chagum?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.02,0:02:06.06,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Chagum!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.06,0:02:11.03,Signs,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Episode 24\NThe Last Hope
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.13,0:02:16.77,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What happened to Chagum?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.74,0:02:22.37,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Balsa!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.11,0:02:24.07,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm coming with you!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.81,0:02:25.74,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Come on then!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.12,0:02:35.18,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Calm yourselves!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.02,0:02:38.15,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Remain calm!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.35,0:02:40.66,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Regroup into your teams!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.06,0:02:44.83,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Squads one and two,\Naccompany me in pursuit of the prince...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.83,0:02:46.16,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Hold on there.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.06,0:02:49.07,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Don't be so hasty!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.27,0:02:54.80,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If this place is the land of feasting,\Nthe boy will come back eventually.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.07,0:02:59.31,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,After all, the egg is supposed\Nto hatch at dawn tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.31,0:03:00.48,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Perhaps, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.48,0:03:03.48,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Leave the pursuit to that bunch.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.75,0:03:06.35,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You'll never be able\Nto catch up with them.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.35,0:03:10.62,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What the two of us ought to be\Ndoing is exchanging information.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.52,0:03:12.79,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Am I right?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.19,0:03:15.49,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yes...yes, of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.63,0:03:17.13,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Perhaps you're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.13,0:03:21.73,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Men! Set up bonfires\Nalong the pond's periphery!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.00,0:03:26.74,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We mustn't allow the Rarunga to\Nattack again when the prince returns!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.07,0:03:28.91,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Make your preparations at once!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.91,0:03:30.31,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.88,0:03:38.98,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Mistress Torogai, the epitaphs\Nhidden beneath the palace...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.98,0:03:42.65,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...say much the same thing\Nthat you told us in Toumi village.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.65,0:03:46.49,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It says the guardian of the spirit\Nwill be ripped apart by the egg-eater.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.46,0:03:49.39,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,However, we had\Nthe good fortune...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.39,0:03:52.86,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...to learn that Rarunga\Ncould be kept at bay with fire.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.03,0:03:59.24,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Could you tell me\Nexactly what it said?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.00,0:04:04.57,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,On this day 200 years ago,\Nour founding father used fire...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.57,0:04:09.11,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...to rescue a Yakoo child\Nnamed Sigul from the Rarunga.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.21,0:04:13.38,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,However, the egg exists\Nbetween Nayug and Sagu...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.38,0:04:15.65,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...not within the child itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.65,0:04:20.79,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Apparently, the Nyunga Ro Chaga has\Nno means to deliver the egg himself.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.16,0:04:27.06,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,As I thought, the only way for the egg\Nto come out is if it's eaten by a Rarunga?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.23,0:04:29.23,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Master Star Reader\NNanai seems to...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.23,0:04:32.84,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...have observed the\Nevents in minute detail.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.84,0:04:35.34,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,He and a Yakooan magic weaver\Nwho had accompanied them...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.34,0:04:38.04,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...tried desperately\Nto extract the egg.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.44,0:04:43.35,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And then, just when their spell\Nwas on the verge of success...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.61,0:04:46.12,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...the child was torn\Napart by a Rarunga...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.12,0:04:48.25,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...which had come\Nonce again from Nayug.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.25,0:04:51.12,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What became of\Nthe egg after that?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.99,0:04:55.39,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Moments after the Rarunga tore\Nthe child apart and swallowed it...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.39,0:05:00.03,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...they witnessed an orb glowing\Nwith a blue light shoot from its mouth.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.00,0:05:05.13,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,After that, something called\Na "nahjil" carried it away.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.40,0:05:09.81,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,However, this term "nahjil"\Ndoes not exist in our language.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.01,0:05:12.01,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Do you have any idea\Nwhat this nahjil might be?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.91,0:05:14.18,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.71,0:05:17.98,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It means a nahji, I expect.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.58,0:05:21.35,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The birds in the\NYakoo rice-planting song.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.35,0:05:22.55,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.02,0:05:25.66,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Damn it all...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.66,0:05:30.16,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I had hoped that the answers you\Nbrought would answer everything...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.49,0:05:33.43,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...but they've left us with more\Ndifficult problems than ever.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.43,0:05:36.83,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Then you do not know any spells\Nto extract the egg, either?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.07,0:05:43.27,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,No. I won't have any idea what\NI might try until it actually happens.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.27,0:05:46.68,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And even assuming that\NI manage to extract the egg...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.68,0:05:49.25,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...who's to say that\Na nahji will come to us?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.25,0:05:50.35,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That's true...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.05,0:05:52.58,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,This isn't good...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.09,0:06:01.86,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Damn. I can't even\Nfind any footprints.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.23,0:06:05.76,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It's possible that Chagum\Nis moving from tree to tree.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.03,0:06:07.00,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Tree to tree?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.00,0:06:09.53,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Right. You saw him\Ndo it too, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.80,0:06:12.50,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Chagum ran on top of the water.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.00,0:06:18.21,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The egg intends to lead the Rarunga\Non a chase until dawn to protect itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.47,0:06:22.28,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That's probably also the reason why\NChagum ate that shigu salua flower.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.61,0:06:25.15,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The scent of flowers\Nattracts creatures of Nayug.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.15,0:06:26.15,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Also...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.13,0:06:39.53,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You lost sight of the prince too?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.96,0:06:41.70,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Meaning that you didn't\Nhave any luck, either?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.70,0:06:42.60,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.93,0:06:46.64,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We chased after the Rarunga,\Nbut it suddenly disappeared.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.84,0:06:51.31,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And as you said, Prince Chagum\Nfled by leaping from tree to tree.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.57,0:06:54.21,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,He moved so quickly that not\Neven we could keep up with him.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.21,0:06:57.55,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You there. Where do you\Nbelieve the prince is headed?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.08,0:07:02.08,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know for sure, but if Aoike\Nreally is the land of feasting...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.08,0:07:04.12,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...he might return\Nby daybreak.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.59,0:07:08.29,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,At any rate, Chagum is under\Nthe control of the egg right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.69,0:07:11.53,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Wandering around the forest\Nisn't going to accomplish anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.96,0:07:15.00,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Commander, should we return\Nto Aoike for the time being?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.26,0:07:18.80,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We mustn't! Even if His Highness\Nreally is being controlled by the egg...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.80,0:07:21.94,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...what if he is\Nattacked by a Rarunga?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.14,0:07:24.97,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm also against returning to Aoike.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.41,0:07:27.24,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If that's the land of feasting...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.24,0:07:32.38,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...and he's running from the Rarunga\Nuntil sunrise, why would he do that?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.52,0:07:38.19,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,He deliberately fled into the forest.\NDon't you think there's a reason?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.02,0:07:43.46,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Indeed. I agree with\Nwhat the spear-wielder says.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.83,0:07:45.53,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,According to Master\NShuga's deductions...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.53,0:07:48.30,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...the Rarunga would\Nnot attack until dawn.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.40,0:07:50.73,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,There must have been\Nsome sort of miscalculation.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.73,0:07:54.80,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,In which case, our only option\Nis to locate Chagum ourselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.90,0:07:56.14,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So it would seem.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.56,0:08:24.47,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Where do you intend to go?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.48,0:08:35.48,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You're going to follow that\Nriverbed farther upstream?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.56,0:08:54.23,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The Rarunga will come again...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.64,0:09:39.71,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,it's a good thing that we\Ndon't have to fight those people.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.18,0:09:43.61,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It's clear even to me\Njust how skilled they are.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.75,0:09:45.08,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You think so?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.25,0:09:51.72,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Spear-wielder.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.12,0:09:56.53,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,There's one question I had been\Nmeaning to ask if we ever met again.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.36,0:10:03.27,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That first time we crossed swords,\Nour team of four failed to kill you.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.70,0:10:06.97,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I do not believe we were overly\Nconfident in our superior numbers.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.97,0:10:10.04,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Why didn't you kill us that night?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.94,0:10:15.01,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I believe you could have killed\Nall of us had you wished to.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.79,0:10:27.19,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,No reason in particular.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.59,0:10:32.53,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I had just agreed to save someone, so\NI thought it would defeat the purpose...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.53,0:10:35.26,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...if I killed someone\Nelse in the process.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.20,0:10:39.57,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.30,0:10:43.97,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If it had been because\Nyou were looking down on us...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.97,0:10:47.04,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...I had planned to settle the matter\Nhere and now to redeem our honor.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.41,0:10:50.38,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But it would seem we\Nwere outmatched all along.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.38,0:10:54.28,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Soon, when we find ourselves\Nin a cataclysmic battle...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.28,0:10:57.49,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...we will follow you\Nwithout hesitation.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.56,0:11:02.66,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Stop that. You're embarrassing me.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.73,0:11:14.24,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,My magic allows me to\Nsee the egg inside the boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.37,0:11:18.14,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,However, I've never\Nbeen able to touch it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.61,0:11:23.61,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Even so, if we can find some other\Nway to interact with Nayug, maybe I...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.95,0:11:28.28,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What was that?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.02,0:11:30.32,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What's that commotion?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.69,0:11:33.66,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Master Shuga!\NIs Master Shuga here?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.00,0:11:46.77,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Master Shuga, I have a\Nmessage from Master Gakai.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.97,0:11:49.97,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Aoike is not the land of feasting!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.07,0:11:54.54,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Saanan, the land of feasting,\Nis located somewhere else entirely!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.61,0:11:57.28,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What? What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.61,0:12:03.25,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,He says that Saanan's precise\Nlocation is recorded on these tablets.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.09,0:12:10.16,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If this isn't the land of feasting,\Nwe're in trouble...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.39,0:12:11.19,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Indeed.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.56,0:12:14.90,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'd say that it's about\Nthree bells before dawn.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.76,0:12:20.84,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I can't believe it. How could we have\Nmissed something so important?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.97,0:12:26.98,Signs,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Moribito Guardian of the Spirit
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.48,0:12:28.74,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Incredible!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.91,0:12:34.95,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Written here is a scene that is identical\Nto what we witnessed not long ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.45,0:12:37.42,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Two hundred years ago,\Nanother child ate a flower...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.42,0:12:40.89,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...and disappeared into the forest,\Nleading the Rarunga after him.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.76,0:12:46.23,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Also, it would seem that in Nayug,\Nthis location is the Rarunga's lair.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.50,0:12:51.40,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The child ate the flower to get\Nthe Rarunga to follow it, then?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.40,0:12:52.50,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.30,0:12:57.91,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Also, it says that Saanan is some\Ntwenty nan to the north of here.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.27,0:13:02.85,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Twenty nan? We'll be lucky to\Ncover that distance by daybreak.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.85,0:13:05.68,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I will gather my forces,\Nand we will leave at once.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.68,0:13:12.19,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Right, but first we should tell those\Nwho went on ahead about this.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.19,0:13:12.86,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But we--
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.86,0:13:14.12,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But we--\NCalm down.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.42,0:13:19.96,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Luck is still on our side, since\Nthat nitwit Tanda wouldn't leave her.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.33,0:13:25.07,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If this pond is a location that overlaps\Nwith Nayug, this ought to work.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.50,0:13:28.54,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Commander.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.57,0:13:31.21,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Seems to be no doubt about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.21,0:13:32.01,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,No, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.07,0:13:33.88,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,They lead up that riverbed.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.28,0:13:39.18,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If he's come back\Ndown to the ground...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.18,0:13:42.38,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...he might be planning to\Nattract the egg-eater again.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.38,0:13:44.25,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Let's try following the river.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.25,0:13:45.05,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.94,0:14:03.77,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,All right, it worked...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.61,0:14:08.41,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Now we have to pray\Nthat Tanda spots it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.88,0:14:13.38,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If those young pups of yours\Nhave joined forces with Balsa...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.38,0:14:15.35,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...they'll probably turn up too.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.35,0:14:18.72,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,They'll be a lot more\Nuseful than this bunch here.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.05,0:14:23.69,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It'll be a lucky break for us if\Nthey reach Saanan before we do.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.30,0:14:32.07,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You know how to ride a horse?\NWe'll ride on ahead on that.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.30,0:14:35.04,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Tell your troops to follow after us.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.24,0:14:38.91,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We can't let that\Negg hatch without us!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.17,0:14:40.11,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Right!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.03,0:14:59.03,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Who said that?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.90,0:15:09.34,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Balsa!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.97,0:15:11.24,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Come look at this!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.94,0:15:13.51,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Did he find something?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.74,0:15:15.84,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go check it out.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.88,0:15:21.78,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What's the matter?\NDid you find something?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.15,0:15:24.09,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Someone is calling me.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.60,0:15:43.84,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...Tanda...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.71,0:15:50.55,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Y-Yes, that's right.\NMy name is Tanda.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.31,0:15:53.38,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...Torogai...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.25,0:16:00.22,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...Chagum...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.72,0:16:03.03,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The land of feasting is\Ntwenty nan to the north.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.03,0:16:05.06,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Chagum is headed there too.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.06,0:16:06.43,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Is that all?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.28,0:16:21.81,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What in the world are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.15,0:16:29.22,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I just got a message\Nfrom the mistress.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.42,0:16:31.69,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I know where Chagum is headed.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.05,0:16:33.96,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Chagum is headed for\Na place called Saanan...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.96,0:16:35.96,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...one of the Aoyumi's headwaters.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.33,0:16:39.03,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Apparently, that's the\Nreal land of feasting.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.36,0:16:40.93,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Your hunch was right, Balsa.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.36,0:16:44.63,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Which means we have\Nto reach it before dawn!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.80,0:16:49.71,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It's less than three bells to sunrise!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.09,0:17:09.22,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,They're following\Non our heels, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.22,0:17:12.26,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. They are an elite,\Nhandpicked force.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.39,0:17:14.83,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I am certain that they\Nwill catch up with us.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.06,0:17:17.97,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If we get there,\Nand it's just us two...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.60,0:17:20.57,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Certainly not an ideal scenario...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.57,0:17:24.64,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...but if that should be the case,\NI shall protect the prince myself!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.78,0:18:08.95,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Look at this.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.06,0:18:18.19,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, it's Chagum's.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.93,0:18:25.60,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It hasn't been long since\Nhe passed through here.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.93,0:18:52.89,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Out of the way!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.46,0:18:57.10,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It's those two\Ncreatures from before.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.37,0:18:59.23,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Are they looking for the prince?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.47,0:19:00.57,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Looks that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.80,0:19:04.07,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,They're much more visible than\Nthey were this afternoon, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.52,0:19:20.99,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Did they catch his scent?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.71,0:19:38.61,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We can see them...\Nwhy can't we hit them?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.05,0:19:53.42,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Damn!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.16,0:19:59.83,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It's no use! It won't work unless the\NRarunga is trying to interact with Sagu!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.63,0:21:05.66,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Tanda!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.42,0:21:33.96,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Tanda!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.36,0:22:12.16,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What did you do?\NHow could you touch it?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.33,0:22:14.46,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,These.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.00,0:22:17.90,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,When the Rarunga\Nappeared at Aoike...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.90,0:22:21.74,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...the only things it affected were the\Nroots and blossoms of these flowers.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.74,0:22:24.44,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I thought I should bring\Nsome along just in case.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.44,0:22:26.64,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Looks like it was the right call.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.64,0:22:32.31,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If we eat these like Chagum did,\Nwe'll be able to touch the Rarunga too.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.82,0:22:37.69,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The downside is that we'll also be\Nat risk of being killed by those things.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:39.52,0:22:40.52,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You're hurt!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.96,0:22:49.16,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Balsa, these flowers\Nare our last hope.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.56,0:22:52.13,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Can you use these\Nto save Chagum?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.30,0:22:53.20,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.68,0:23:13.02,ED,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,As I sat huddled and alone, holding\Nback the tears on those nights...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.02,0:23:20.16,ED,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,When it felt like I was about\Nto succumb to my doubts...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.16,0:23:25.43,ED,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...there you were,\Nat my side before I knew it.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.43,0:23:32.77,ED,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It was none other than you\Nwho was there for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.77,0:23:47.06,ED,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I keep wishing, "I want to be strong."\NI stumble and hurt myself again.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.06,0:23:56.43,ED,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But because I have you to believe in,\NI can get back to my feet.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.43,0:24:03.20,ED,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I simply want to tell\Nmy dear one, "Thank you. "
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.20,0:24:08.34,ED,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,At the top of my lungs,\Nagain and again.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.34,0:24:16.72,ED,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I call out to my precious loved one.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.72,0:24:20.92,ED,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Is my voice reaching you?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.92,0:24:29.16,ED,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,In this world that always changes,\Nhuman warmth never does.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:29.16,0:24:39.47,ED,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm certain I sensed the presence\Nof the one that I hold dear.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:41.98,0:24:45.48,Signs,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Next Time
Dialogue: 0,0:24:43.21,0:24:45.78,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,After the passage of a hundred\Nyears, the promised day dawns.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:46.58,0:24:49.55,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Saanan is a place of celebration\Nwhere living things go to kindle new life.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:50.75,0:24:51.97,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Next time, "Celebration."
Dialogue: 0,0:24:51.99,0:24:56.99,Signs,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Episode 25\NCelebration
Dialogue: 0,0:24:53.59,0:24:56.49,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Father, child, and mother\Nwill celebrate together there.
